<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May 28,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Boxers increasing. Nine Methodist converts brutally murdered at Pachow.
                            The movement has developed into open rebellion. Chinese Government is
                            trying but apparently is unable to suppress it. Many soldiers disloyal.
                            Several railroad bridges and stations near Pekin burned. Legations have
                            ordered guards.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>